EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to compensation of the mayor, public advocate, members of the city council, borough presidents, comptroller and district attorneys.
EventItemMatterName: Compensation of the mayor, public advocate, members of the city council, borough presidents, comptroller and district attorneys.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of Finance and the Environmental Control Board to implement Chapter 45 of the Laws of New York for the year 2000 in relation to the enforcement of Environmental Control Board judgments against certain owners for building code violations.
EventItemMatterName: The enforcement of Environmental Control Board judgments against certain owners for building code violations.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to make Veterans Day a permanent school holiday.
EventItemMatterName: NYC Department of Education to make Veterans Day a permanent school holiday.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring the New York city department of education to report on the status of science labs in public schools.
EventItemMatterName: NYC Dep't of education to report on the status of science labs in public schools.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring the New York city department of education to report on the progress of preparatory programs for students who seek admission to specialized senior high schools.
EventItemMatterName: NYC Dep't of education to report on the progress of preparatory programs for students who seek admission to specialized senior high schools.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass A. 6502, an act to amend the executive law in relation to enacting the SAFETY act, which would prohibit discrimination and harassment in New York State Office of Children and Family Services facilities and require that facility staff be trained to respond appropriately to such behavior.
EventItemMatterName: Enacting the SAFETY Act (A.6502)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass the Safe Harbour for Exploited Youth Act, S.4423/A.6597, which would amend the social services law, the family court act, and the penal law in relation to services for sexually exploited youth.
EventItemMatterName: Pass the Safe Harbour for Exploited Youth Act (S.4423/A.6597)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass A.6334-A/S. 6877-A, which would create the Office of the Child Advocate to oversee the New York State Office of Children and Family Services.
EventItemMatterName: Create the Office of the Child Advocate (A.6334-A/S. 6877-A)
